obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (31777)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370&sectionId=31777&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Indian Soldiers`
  line `(Litigation) Act, 1925.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2***.]`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on the first day of April, 1925.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by A.O. 1950 for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 62 of 1956, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (31778)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370&sectionId=31778&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "Court" means a Court other than a Criminal Court and includes any such tribunal or other`
  line `authority as may be specified by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette being`
  line `a tribunal or authority which is empowered by law to receive evidence on any matter pending before`
  line `it and on the basis of such evidence to determine, after hearing the parties before it, the rights and`
  line `obligations of the parties in relation to such matter;]`
  line
  line `(b)" Indian soldier" means any person subject to ^2[the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950), or the Air`
  line `Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950)] ^3[, or the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957)];`
  line
  line `(c) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(d) "proceeding" includes any suit, appeal or application;`
  line
  line `^3[(e) any reference to a decree or order of a Court shall be deemed to include a reference to a`
  line `judgment, determination or award of a Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 1970, s. 2, for cl. (a) (w.e.f. 29-5-1970).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule., for certain words.`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 1970, s. 2. (w.e.f. 29-5-1970).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (31779)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Circumstances in which an Indian soldier shall be deemed to be serving under special conditions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370&sectionId=31779&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this. Act, an Indian soldier shall be deemed to be or, as the case may be,`
  line `to have been serving--`
  line
  line `(a) under special conditions--when he is or has been serving under war conditions, or overseas,`
  line `or at any place ^1[beyond India] ^2[or at any such place within India as may be specified by the Central`
  line `Government by notification in the Official Gazette];`
  line
  line `(b) under war conditions--when he is or has been, at any time during the continuance of any`
  line `hostilities declared by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette to constitute a`
  line `state of war for the purposes of this Act or at any time during a period of six months thereafter--,`
  line
  line `(i) serving out of India,`
  line
  line `(ii) under orders to proceed on field service,`
  line
  line `(iii) serving with any unit which is for the time being mobilised, or`
  line
  line `(iv) serving under conditions which, in the opinion of the prescribed authority, preclude him`
  line `from obtaining leave of absence to enable him to attend a Court as a party to any proceeding, or`
  line `when he is or has been at any other time serving under conditions service under which has been`
  line `declared by the Central Government by notification in the Official Gazette to be service under`
  line `war conditions; and`
  line
  line `^3[(c) overseas--when he is or has been serving in any place outside India (other than Ceylon) the`
  line `journey between which and ^4[India] is ordinarily undertaken wholly or in part by sea.`
  line
  line `^5[Explanation.--For the purposes of this section and with effect from the 3rd day of September, 1939,`
  line `1939, a soldier who is or has been a prisoner of war shall be deemed to be or to have been serving under`
  line `war conditions.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for certain words.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 1970, s. 3.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for clause(c).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the A.O. 1948, for "British India".`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Ordinance 64 of 1942, s. 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (31780)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Particulars to be furnished in plaints, applications or appeals to Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370&sectionId=31780&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `If any person`
  line `presenting any plaint, application or appeal to any Court has reason to believe that any adverse party is an`
  line `Indian soldier who is serving under special conditions, he shall state the fact in his plaint, application or`
  line appeal.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (31781)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power of Collector to intervene in case of unrepresented Indian soldier.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370&sectionId=31781&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `If any Collector has`
  line `reason to believe that any Indian soldier, who ordinarily resides or has property in his district and who is a`
  line `party to any proceeding pending before any Court, is unable to appear therein, the Collector may certify`
  line `the facts in the prescribed manner to the Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (31782)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Notice to be given in case of unrepresented Indian soldier.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370&sectionId=31782&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] If a Collector has certified`
  line `under section 5, or if the Court has reason to believe, that an Indian soldier, who is a party to any`
  line `proceeding pending before it, is unable to appear therein, and if the soldier is not represented by any`
  line `person duly authorised to appear, plead or act on his behalf, the Court shall suspend the proceeding, and`
  line `shall give notice thereof in the prescribed manner to the prescribed authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Court may refrain from suspending the proceeding and issuing the notice if--`
  line
  line `(a) the proceeding is a suit, appeal or application instituted or made by the soldier, alone or`
  line `conjointly with others with the object of enforcing a right of pre-emption, or`
  line
  line `(b) the interests of the soldier in the proceeding are, in the opinion of the Court, either identical`
  line `with those of any other party to the proceeding and adequately represented by such other party or`
  line `merely of a formal nature.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) If it appears to the Court before which any proceeding is pending that an Indian soldier though`
  line `not a party to the proceeding is materially concerned in the outcome of the proceeding and that his`
  line `interests are likely to be prejudiced by his inability to attend, the Court may suspend the proceeding and`
  line `shall give notice thereof in the prescribed manner to the prescribed authority.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 6 renumbered as sub-section (1) of that section by s. 3, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s.3, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (31783)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Postponement of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370&sectionId=31783&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `If, on receipt of a notice under section 6, the prescribed`
  line `authority certifies in the prescribed manner to the Court in which the proceeding is pending that the`
  line `soldier in respect of whom the notice was given is serving under special conditions, and that a`
  line `postponement of the proceeding in respect of the soldier is necessary, in the interests of justice, the Court`
  line `shall thereupon postpone the proceeding in respect of the soldier for the prescribed period, or, if no period`
  line `has been prescribed, for such period as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (31784)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Court may proceed when no certificate received.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370&sectionId=31784&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `If, after issue of a notice under section 6, the`
  line `prescribed authority either certifies that the soldier is not serving under special conditions or that such postponement is not necessary, or fails to certify, in the case of a soldier resident in the district in which`
  line `the Court is situate within two months or, in any other case, within three months from the date of the issue`
  line `of the notice that such postponement is necessary, the Court may, if it thinks fit, continue the proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (31785)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Postponement of proceedings against Indian soldier on leave.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `. Subs. by Ordinance 64 of 1942, s. 4, "for section 6".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370&sectionId=31785&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `When any document`
  line `purporting to be signed by the Commanding Officer of an Indian soldier who is a party to any proceeding`
  line `is produced by or on behalf of the soldier before the Court in which the proceeding is pending and is to`
  line `the effect that the soldier--`
  line
  line `(a) is on leave of absence for a period not exceeding two months, and is on the expiration of his`
  line `leave to proceed on service under special conditions, or`
  line
  line `(b) is on sick leave for a period not exceeding three months, and is on the expiration of his leave`
  line `to rejoin his unit with a view to proceeding on service under special conditions,`
  line
  line `the proceeding in respect of such soldier may, in any case such as is referred to in the proviso to`
  line `^1[sub-section (1) of section 6] and shall, in any other case, be postponed in the manner provided in`
  line `section 7.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (31786)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Power to set aside decrees and orders, passed against an Indian soldier serving under war or special conditions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370&sectionId=31786&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any proceeding before a Court in which a decree or order has been passed`
  line `against any Indian soldier ^1*** whilst he was serving under any special conditions, the soldier ^2[or, if he`
  line `is dead, his legal representative] may apply to the Court which passed the decree or order for an order to`
  line `set aside the same, and, if the Court, after giving an opportunity to the opposite party of being heard, is`
  line `satisfied that the interests of justice require that the decree or order should be set aside as against the`
  line `soldier, the Court shall, subject to such conditions, if any, as it thinks fit to impose, make an order`
  line accordingly.
  line
  line `^3[(2) The period of limitation for an application under sub-section (1) shall be ninety days from the`
  line `date of the decree or order, or, where the summons or notice was not duly served on the soldier in the`
  line `proceeding in which the decree or order was passed, from the date on which the applicant had knowledge`
  line `of the decree or order; and the provisions of section 5 of the Indian Limitation Act, 1908`
  line `(9 of 1908) shall apply to such applications.]`
  line
  line `(3) When the decree or order in respect of which an application under sub-section (1) is made is of`
  line `such a nature that it cannot be set aside as against the soldier only, it may be set aside as against all or any`
  line `of the parties against whom it has been made.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a Court sets aside a decree or order under this section, it shall appoint a day for proceeding`
  line `with the suit, appeal or application, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Certain words omitted by s. 5, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 5, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (31787)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Modification of law of limitation where Indian soldier or his legal representative is a party.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370&sectionId=31787&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[11. Modification of law of limitation where Indian soldier or his legal representative is a`
  line `party.--In computing the period of limitation prescribed by sub-section (2) of section 10 of this Act, the`
  line `Indian Limitation Act, 1908 (9 of 1908) or any other law for the time being in force, for any suit, appeal`
  line `or application to a court, any party to which is or has been an Indian soldier, or is the legal representative`
  line `of an Indian soldier, the period during which the soldier has been serving under any special conditions,`
  line `and, if the soldier has died while so serving, the period from the date of his death to the date on which`
  line `official intimation thereof was sent to his next-of-kin by the authorities in India, shall be excluded:`
  line
  line `Provided that this section shall not apply in the case of any suit, appeal or application instituted or`
  line `made with the object of enforcing a right of pre-emption ^2[`
  line `^3[except where the said right accrues in such`
  line `circumstances, and is in respect of agricultural land and village immovable property situated in any such`
  line `area] as the Central Government may, by notification in the official Gazette, specify in this behalf].`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 6, for s. 11.`
  line
  line `2. Added by Ordinance 14 of 1944, s. 2.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 1946, s. 2, for certain words.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (31788)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of Court to refer questions to prescribed authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Ordinance 64 of 1942, s. 7.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370&sectionId=31788&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[12. Power of Court to refer questions to prescribed authorities.--If any Court is in doubt`
  line `whether, for the purposes of section 10 or section 11, an Indian soldier is or was at any particular time`
  line `serving under special conditions, or has died while so serving, or as to the date of such death or as to the`
  line `date on which official intimation of such death was sent to his next-of-kin by the authorities in India, the`
  line `Court may refer the point for the decision of the prescribed authority, and the certificate of that authority`
  line `shall be conclusive evidence on the point.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (31789)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Rule making power.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370&sectionId=31789&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The ^2[Central Government] ^3*** may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette make ruless to provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner and form in which any notice or certificate under this Act shall be given;`
  line
  line `(b) the period for which proceedings or any class of proceedings shall be postponed under`
  line `section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) the persons who shall be the prescribed authorities for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(e) generally, any matters incidental to the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 13 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  line
  line `3. The words "after consulting the High Court concerned" omitted by Act 23 of 1970, s. 4.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (31790)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to apply the provisions of the Act to other persons in the service of the Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370&sectionId=31790&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00023_1925_1523345043370
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] ^2[As respects the State Public Services, the State Government, and in other cases,`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that all or any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall apply to any other class of persons in the service of Government specified in`
  line `such notification in the same, manner as they apply to Indian soldiers,`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Where, under this section, the State Government has directed that all or any of the provisions of`
  line `this Act shall apply to any class of persons in the service of Government, the powers vested in the Central`
  line `Government by section 3 and section 13 shall be exercised in respect of that class of persons by the`
  line `State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
